Ethiopian Airlines last Friday, July 1, 2022, added Athens in Greece, Chennai in India, Damman in Saudi Arabia, Jakarta in Indonesia and Bahrain to its already 127 strong international destinations. A statement by the media consultant to the airline said that these new destinations join the double daily flights to Mumbai, India and 10 weekly flights to Delhi, India. Recently Ethiopian Airlines started another flight to Washington DC from Lome, Togo offering more options to its Nigerian passengers. Ethiopian Airlines flies from 4 airports in Nigeria; Lagos, Abuja, Kano and Enugu. Also, the airline has opened a 5-star terminal hotel inside the Bole Airport. The hotel, Skylight In-Terminal Hotel inside Addis Ababa Bole International Airport Terminal 02 is just a short walk to the departure gates for boarding “B,” the airline said in a statement. Travellers needing a pre-flight freshen up or those with shorter stopovers, it said could use the hotel’s 24-hour fitness centre, spacious, pet-friendly rooms and suites with luxury bedding, flat-screen TVs. Ethiopian Skylight In-Terminal Hotel has 97 tranquil rooms in five categories, each featuring modern essentials for a seamless stay. A Skylight Suite has additional space with a living or dining area. The Hub Restaurant it sad is located between both room wings above concourse “B,” but stated that guest must have an international departure flight from Terminal 2 only.